<h2>AI Content and SEO</h2>
<p><strong>16. 86% of top-ranking Google pages are still human-authored.</strong> Only 14% of top results are AI-generated. (Source: <a href="https://mynewitguys.com/what-percentage-of-online-content-is-ai-generated-in-2025/">MyNewITGuys</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>17. 86.5% of content in the top 20 search results is at least partially AI-generated.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/what-percentage-of-new-content-is-ai-generated/">Ahrefs</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>18. Near-zero correlation (0.011) between AI content and ranking penalties.</strong> Ahrefs found no measurable penalty for AI-generated content across 600,000 pages. (Source: <a href="https://snezzi.com/blog/does-google-ignore-ai-content-what-the-data-says-in-2025/">Snezzi / Ahrefs</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>19. In a 16-month experiment, 71% of AI pages indexed within 36 days.</strong> But by 3 months, only 3% remained in the top 100. (Source: <a href="https://searchengineland.com/ai-generated-content-google-search-experiment-472234">Search Engine Land</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>20. 97% of AI Overviews cite at least 1 source from the top 20 organic results.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://seomator.com/blog/ai-seo-statistics">SEOmator</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>21. Ranking #1 gives a 33.07% chance of being cited in AI Overviews.</strong> Ranking #10 gives only a 13.04% chance. (Source: <a href="https://seomator.com/blog/ai-seo-statistics">SEOmator</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>22. 98% of marketers plan higher AI SEO spend in 2026.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://www.typeface.ai/blog/content-marketing-statistics">Typeface</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>23. Google has ramped up manual actions for "scaled content abuse" since June 2025.</strong> Low-quality AI content at volume triggers enforcement. (Source: <a href="https://maintouch.com/blogs/does-google-penalize-ai-generated-content">MainTouch</a>, 2026)</p>
